<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 pb-16 pt-14">
  <p class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ppq-red">About the brand</p>
  <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl uppercase leading-tight md:text-5xl">Pop Punk Queso started as a playlist. Now it's a scene-friendly music brand.</h1>
  <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-ppq-muted">
    The origin story is simple: one playlist, too many songs, and a strong opinion about what actually deserves your repeat button.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8 px-4 pb-16 text-base leading-8 text-ppq-ink">
  <article class="rounded-3xl border border-ppq-ink/10 bg-white p-6 md:p-8">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl uppercase">Curated taste, not a dump folder</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Pop Punk Queso is built around curation with intent. If a track makes it in, it earned the slot.
      We cut filler fast and keep the rotation tight enough to stay replayable.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="rounded-3xl border border-ppq-ink/10 bg-white p-6 md:p-8">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl uppercase">The lane</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Pop punk is the center line. Adjacent energy is always welcome: emo catharsis, ska bounce,
      indie side quests, and skate-punk velocity when it fits the mood.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="rounded-3xl border border-ppq-ink/10 bg-white p-6 md:p-8">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl uppercase">Why the website exists</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Social posts disappear. Algorithms drift. The site is home base: updates, articles, direct update alerts,
      and future merch drops/events in one place.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <%= link_to "Listen", listen_path, class: "rounded-full bg-ppq-red px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-white hover:bg-red-700" %>
      <%= link_to "Read updates", updates_path, class: "rounded-full border border-ppq-ink px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide hover:bg-ppq-cream" %>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>
